(11, 'Week 11', '&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n# WEEK 11\n\n**Name:** Clarence Jake Bonilla\n\n**Week:** 11\n\n**Instructor:** Mr. Ronnel Dela Cruz\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**I. Inclusive Dates you worked:**\n\n| DATE | START TIME | END TIME | HOURS RENDERED |\n| :---:  | :---: | :---: | :---: | \n| 4/29/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs  |\n| 5/01/2024  | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm | 8 hrs   |\n| 4/02/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n| 4/03/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n| 4/04 /2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n|  |  | TOTAL HOURS RENDERED | 40 hrs  |\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**II. OJT Location:** Baloc Road, Brgy. San Ignacio, San Pablo City Laguna 4000\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**III. Weekly Activity Reports:**\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **A. Detailed discussion of what you do every day.**\n\n| Day| Work Discussion |\n| --- | --- |\n|   &emsp; 1   | Today, we tackled another React project by cloning the homepage of the YouTube website ourselves. Utilizing the skills I\\\'ve acquired over the past few months, I successfully recreated the YouTube homepage today.|\n|   &emsp; 2   | Today, I just finished polishing my cloned YouTube project. Since it\\\'s due for grading today, I double checked all the details and data mappings to ensure the details are correct. My instructor will be assessing our projects at 12 pm, so I feel relieved to have completed mine. Additionally, we\\\'re beginning a new project today which is creating a school dashboard.  |\n|   &emsp; 3   |  Today, we kept working on our school dashboard project. We focused on its design and added some features. For example, we made it so that if you double click a row, it shows some information about the user. Right now, it\\\'s not getting data from the database. We finished the design and added some features to the dashboard. After we were done, I pushed the project on my GitHub. |\n|   &emsp; 4   | Today, we continued our school dashboard project, and our instructor introduced us to Formik, TanStack, and Yup. Formik helps in building forms, offering features like error handling, validation, and submissions. TanStack is for managing API requests, and Yup is a JavaScript library for form validation. We also started working on our API today, which was a bit confusing. Our instructor also showed us the Thunder Client extension, which lets us test our API, helping us spot any issues. I learned a lot today and gained up new skills and knowledge. |\n|   &emsp; 5   |  Today, I created the API for Netflix, setting up new tables, controllers, and a database for each data category within Netflix. After completing all the necessary components for the API, I proceeded to test it using the Thunder Client extension. However, during the testing phase, I encountered issues with my API. Through Thunder Client\\\'s error, I learned about the specific problems and errors I was facing, such as forgetting to input the Authentication key and forgetting to update some information in the API. Despite these problems, I managed to finish my tasks and learned a lot of things. |\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **B. New Experiences**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I’ve had new experiences, like learning React and creating dashboard with Formik, TanStack, and Yup. Even though I faced some problems like debugging errors and testing with Thunder Client, I saw them as a opportunity to learn and grow my skills.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **C. Skills and knowledge areas that you need to improve**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; This week showed me areas where I need to improve my skills and knowledge. I need to enhance my knowledge in making API and using tools like Thunder Client to prevent future mistakes like forgetting to input authentication keys. I also need to improve my database skills and how I handle and fixed errors.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **D. Plans for improving your performance**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; To enhance my performance, I plan to practice creating APIs and using testing tools like Thunder Client regularly. I also plan to focus on improving database skills and learning how to handle errors more faster.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **E. Situations you observed during the week that were interesting and might be helpful to you in your professional development.**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; This, week I noticed the importance of Testing APIs properly before using them. Also, I realized the importance of double checking information when setting up APIs to avoid errors\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **F. Summary Statement**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; This week gives me a valuable learning experiences. I created API and test it using the Thunder Client extension in Visual Studio Code. Despite encountering many problems and errors, I’m determined to improve my skills in React, API, and database that will make me grow.', '2024-05-31', 1, '2024-05-31 09:13:11', '2024-05-31 09:12:10'),
(12, 'Week 12', '&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n# WEEK 12\n\n**Name:** Clarence Jake Bonilla\n\n**Week:** 12\n\n**Instructor:** Mr. Ronnel Dela Cruz\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**I. Inclusive Dates you worked:**\n\n| DATE | START TIME | END TIME | HOURS RENDERED |\n| :---:  | :---: | :---: | :---: | \n| 5/06/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs  |\n| 5/07/2024  | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/08/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/09/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/10 /2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/11 /2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n|  |  | TOTAL HOURS RENDERED | 48 hrs  |\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**II. OJT Location:** Baloc Road, Brgy. San Ignacio, San Pablo City Laguna 4000\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**III. Weekly Activity Reports:**\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **A. Detailed discussion of what you do every day.**\n\n| Day| Work Discussion |\n| --- | --- |\n|   &emsp; 1   | Today, we continued working on some parts of the school dashboard, and then we moved on to another project, converting our personal portfolios into React. I completed the banner section, header, and footer of my portfolio today. |\n|   &emsp; 2   | Today, I updated the color and added sections that were missing to my portfolio, such as my projects and experiences. I completed adding all sections today. Additionally, I made some design edits to my portfolio to suit it better with my preferences. After finishing, I pushed the updated project to my GitHub repository. |\n|   &emsp; 3   |  Today, our instructor gave us time to edit parts of our portfolios. After making the necessary changes, we resumed our previous project which is the school dashboard. We implemented CRUD functions, allowing the dashboard to create, read, update, and delete information from the database within the UI. Additionally, we added toast messages to that shows when the CRUD functions are successfully working. I encountered some issues such as the toast messages not appearing and the CRUD functions not functioning properly. With the guidance of our instructor and the assistance of my work mates, I managed to resolve these issues. |\n|   &emsp; 4   | Today, we continued working on our dashboard project. We implemented a search feature and included new inputs in Formik for student gender and email. However, adding new inputs in Formik won\\\'t function properly if the database lacks corresponding columns for this data. So, we updated our REST API code and added new columns to our database to allow these changes. Additionally, our instructor introduced us to a more easy and shortest method of passing data using Store context, reducers, and actions. |\n|   &emsp; 5   |  Today, we started a new project that combines my portfolio with a dashboard. The dashboard helps me edit my portfolio by fetching data from the database. If, for example, I want to change a picture or text on my banner, I can do it through the dashboard. It\\\'s where I manage all my portfolio content. Combining these two projects makes my portfolio more dynamic. I ran into a few small problems while working, but I fixed them quickly. |\n|   &emsp; 6   |  Today, my instructor gave me a task which is to print some sections of my portfolio, like the project we worked on yesterday. I successfully added three sections to my portfolio, and they\\\'re functioning well. The data from my database now appears on my portfolio. When I use CRUD functions on my dashboard, the changes reflect on my portfolio too. Additionally, I added a counter page for each section, showing how many items are in each. While working on the project, I encountered some minor errors, but I managed to fix them. |\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **B. New Experiences**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I tried something new this week by combining my school dashboard with my personal portfolio, both built in React. It\\\'s my first time combining two projects at once. Additionally, I experienced a new way of doing CRUD this week. Usually, I use PHP directly in my HTML to perform CRUD operations, but this time I gained new knowledge by using a combination of API, React, and PHP.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **C. Skills and knowledge areas that you need to improve**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I need to improve my knowledge in React, specifically in implementing CRUD operations and integrating API. Also enhancing my understanding of database and backend development will strengthen my ability to create more dynamic websites\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **D. Plans for improving your performance**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; To enhance my performance, I plan to dedicate more time to practicing React and deepen my understanding into backend development.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **E. Situations you observed during the week that were interesting and might be helpful to you in your professional development.**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I noticed this week problem solving, and logic is very important when implementing complex projects and adding some features like CRUD operations. Problem solving were also important to solve errors and bugs in my projects.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **F. Summary Statement**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I worked on various project this week, which helped me gain and improves my skills in react, and backend development. I faced some challenges but I managed to resolve it all, thanks to the guidance of my instructor and the help of my workmates. It was a good week with good experiences that motivates me to keep doing better in my work.', '2024-05-31', 1, '2024-05-31 09:28:09', '2024-05-31 09:23:21'),
(13, 'Week 13', '&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n# WEEK 13\n\n**Name:** Clarence Jake Bonilla\n\n**Week:** 13\n\n**Instructor:** Mr. Ronnel Dela Cruz\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**I. Inclusive Dates you worked:**\n\n| DATE | START TIME | END TIME | HOURS RENDERED |\n| :---:  | :---: | :---: | :---: | \n| 5/06/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs  |\n| 5/07/2024  | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/08/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 4 hrs   |\n|  |  | TOTAL HOURS RENDERED | 20 hrs  |\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**II. OJT Location:** Baloc Road, Brgy. San Ignacio, San Pablo City Laguna 4000\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**III. Weekly Activity Reports:**\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **A. Detailed discussion of what you do every day.**\n\n| Day| Work Discussion |\n| --- | --- |\n|   &emsp; 1   | Today, we continued working on our portfolio that we were working on last week. I checked again for my dashboard to see if it was working properly and free from errors and bugs. I’m so glad that it’s free from it. |\n|   &emsp; 2   | Today, I continued working on my portfolio, and then after some hours, our instructor taught us how to upload images using file types in Formik. Before our teacher introduces this way to us, I upload an image by typing the path of the image in an input field. Our teacher way is much easier, and I don’t need to find the path of my image just to upload it, now I can add any image to my PC and then upload it. I learned new things this day. |\n|   &emsp; 3   | Today, we continue working on our portfolio. I redesigned my whole portfolio because I feel like something is lacking in it. I changed the color of it, changed the font size and images, and added other sections to it. |\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **B. New Experiences**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I tried something new this week by uploading an image to my database using the file type in Formik, and it worked properly. I encountered minor problems along the way, but I managed to overcome them.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **C. Skills and knowledge areas that you need to improve**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I still need to improve my knowledge in design and React because I feel that my design skills are still lacking and need improvement. I picked the wrong colors and fonts, and I only noticed it after many days. Also, I need to improve my skills in React because I forgot to use some concepts of React properly.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **D. Plans for improving your performance**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; To enhance my performance, I plan to read documents and online resources about UI and UX. Additionally, I plan to practice my React skills by working on some mini projects.\n\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **E. Situations you observed during the week that were interesting and might be helpful to you in your professional development.**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I observed this week that doing things differently and not sticking to one option gives you more choices that will improved your code. This observation will be helpful to me professionally.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **F. Summary Statement**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; This week, we focused on our portfolios. I checked my dashboard for errors and so glad to find none. Our instructor taught us how to upload images using file types in Formik, which is much easier than my previous method. I also redesigned my entire portfolio, updating colors, font sizes, images, and adding new sections.', '2024-05-31', 1, '2024-05-31 09:35:07', '2024-05-31 09:35:07'),
(14, 'Week 14', '&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n# WEEK 14\n\n**Name:** Clarence Jake Bonilla\n\n**Week:** 14\n\n**Instructor:** Mr. Ronnel Dela Cruz\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**I. Inclusive Dates you worked:**\n\n| DATE | START TIME | END TIME | HOURS RENDERED |\n| :---:  | :---: | :---: | :---: | \n| 5/06/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs  |\n| 5/07/2024  | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/08/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/06/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs  |\n| 5/07/2024  | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm | 8 hrs   |\n| 5/08/2024 | 7:00 am   | 4:00 pm   | 8 hrs   |\n|  |  | TOTAL HOURS RENDERED | 48 hrs  |\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**II. OJT Location:** Baloc Road, Brgy. San Ignacio, San Pablo City Laguna 4000\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n**III. Weekly Activity Reports:**\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **A. Detailed discussion of what you do every day.**\n\n| Day| Work Discussion |\n| --- | --- |\n|   &emsp; 1   | Today, our instructor taught us how to add a login feature to our portfolio dashboard. He shared the code with us and explained it step by step. Also, we added new files to our project such as PHP Mailer, mail-config, and others related to login. We also created a new database and controllers for users. |\n|   &emsp; 2   | Today, we implemented the password creation and forgot password in our project. However, I encountered errors while trying to log in to my dashboard because my user account in the database was inactive which my project did not recognize my account. I’m so glad to fixed my error. Our instructor graded our entire project, including our portfolio with the dashboard and login features. |\n|   &emsp; 3   | Today, we started a new project, which is a blog website using React. We start our project by designing the header, the home page of the website, and the more information page of one blog card.|\n|   &emsp; 4   | Today, we continue fine-tuning our blog website design, and we implemented the dashboard and login that we previously implemented from our previous projects. |\n|   &emsp; 5   | Today, we implemented markdown on our blog, which gives us the freedom to use markdown syntax in React. First, we need to install it by writing npm install react-markdown to our terminal to install the necessary modules that are needed to run the markdown. Now we can add some markdown syntax to our blog. For example, adding ‘## text’ will make the text bold, or *text* will make the text italic. |\n|   &emsp; 6   | Today, my instructor gave me a task, which is to add CRUD to our first React project, which is the clone of the Starbucks the Starbucks menu page. CRUD is working properly and has no errors. |\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **B. New Experiences**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I gained new experience in adding login functionality to a portfolio dashboard, learning to implement password recovery features, and adding PHP Mailer. Additionally, we started a blog website project using React, where I learned\nto use markdown syntax and implemented CRUD operations.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **C. Skills and knowledge areas that you need to improve**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I need to improve my skills in troubleshooting and debugging issues specifically login related issues.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **D. Plans for improving your performance**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; To enhance my performance, I need to dedicate my time in studying debugging techniques to troubleshoot any issues effectively.\n\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **E. Situations you observed during the week that were interesting and might be helpful to you in your professional development.**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; I noticed this that exploring and implementing markdown in the blog project expand my knowledge and skills and displaying contents in React, making it more dynamic that I can also use in my future projects.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp;  **F. Summary Statement**\n\n&emsp;&emsp;&emsp; Throughout this week I worked on various activity, which helped me gain and improves my skills web development. From learning on how to implement login functionality in React, debugging and troubleshooting errors, and implementing markdown. Each activity contributes to my growth as an aspiring web developer.', '2024-05-31', 1, '2024-05-31 09:58:20', '2024-05-31 09:58:20');

